The answer is simple and was obvious to me *after* I asked a
similar question.

Answer:  register your .in-addr.arpa domain with the NIC.

Otherwise, how are the rest of the nameservers supposed to find
you when they're tracing through the in-addr.arpa domain to
find your host addresses?  

Simple, no?
